originalText.text: I have been training with Leigh for almost half a year now, and she is amazing. I was very active prior to working with her, but had developed some injuries that were making it hard for me to stay active. She has helped me build up the strength and balance in the right muscles so that two of my pains appear to be fully gone. I started working with her in person but have since transitioned to virtual. I was initially concerned that virtual would not work out, but I have been pleasantly surprised that it is going great! I would recommend her to anyone who wants a very scientific approach to recovery and strength building.

originalText.text:
If you're looking for a way to get yourself to the next level, Leigh is the person who's going to help you.

She's smart, passionate, curious, thoughtful, and honest and brings that energy to every session while designing and delivering a program that is tailored to you, your skill level, and your goals. Having worked with other trainers in the past, the results I've experienced first hand and have seen following the journeys of her other clients are  evidence that the investment is and will continue to be worth it. Yes, like anything else worth having, you must be willing to show up and do the work, whether it's in person or on your own. Trust if you're on your own, there's a 99.9% chance Leigh's voice will still be echoing in your ear and that's a good thing as the people who inspire, motivate, and keep us in check are always with us.

Her methods will truly help you level up, both inside and outside of the gym. Those tools of focus, trust, consistency, confidence, and drive will stay with you in your normal day to day and make what once seemed challenging less so. Do yourself a favor and reach out, she's worth it and so are you.

originalText.text: In June 2022 I moved to New York, and in the first few months of being in a the city I came to the conclusion that re-investing in my physical health and strength was going to be essential to rebuilding parts of my life from the bottom up. I found Leigh through a friend and from the intro call onwards it was clear that Leigh was not only going to invest in my physical strength, but tailor my training to my holistic needs. Leigh has taught me to believe in my physical strength and in doing so has been essential in redefining how I feel on a daily basis. She is so knowledgable, skilled, personable, and kind and I can’t wait to see how her hypertrophy training continues to build my strength. If you invest in Leigh, she will not hesitate to invest in you — the workouts are hard, but there’s a reason Leigh pushes her clients: she truly believes in the strength people hold in their own bodies. When I started with Leigh I couldn’t squat any weight, I couldn’t deadlift, shoulder press, I didn’t even really feel comfortable in a fitness space for a whole host of reasons. 9 months later I’m squatting 245lbs and coming to sessions excited to keep building my list of PRs, which is a 180 from my mentality at the start of my training. When I first started with Leigh she looked me up and down and said something along the lines of “oh yeah you’re gonna be really strong” and I lacked the confidence in myself to believe her. But she was the first person I felt was truly willing to bet on my ability and strength, so I put my full trust in her. I will forever be glad I did. She has a method to her madness and it will leave you not only feeling far stronger, but will give you a true understanding of what it is that makes you strong. I could not have found a better trainer to work with.

originalText.text:
Leigh is an incredible trainer and coach. I came to her already having a strong foundation in strength and fitness but with a lot of limiting beliefs about my capabilities and a lack of confidence that limited me not only in the gym but in  all aspects of my life. Leigh has not only believed in me but coached me to believe in myself. Working with Leigh,  I have had numerous PRs in my main lifts, she  helped me fix my imbalances in my squat form, analyzed my anatomy to ensure the best and most comfortable set up for my deadlifts, and not only does my body feel stronger all around, my body composition has completely changed for the better. I didn’t change a single thing outside of our sessions together and I actually cut back on the quantity of my training all together. My life no longer revolves around my workouts, they are instead a one hour highlight of my day 3-4 times a week. At 28, I finally feel proud and sexy in my own skin. Training with Leigh has allowed me to embrace so many sides of me.

Leigh’s methodology is a combination of pushing your limits beyond what you think is possible, applying biomechanics to everything you do even if that means getting on the floor to analyze your knee movement and find the exact position and set up that works for your body and not everyone else, mixed with a program that’s fun and different every time so you are working the same movement patterns but don’t get bored week after week. There’s always a reason behind  her programming and she will always explain it.  Her coaching style is being a super smart and strategic coach, your best friend and cheerleader on your hardest days, your therapist (if you want her to be) and the sister that gives you the tough love when you need it the most.

You have changed my life, Leigh, not just in the gym but in how I show up in the world. Forever grateful to you.

originalText.text: Okay, I just finished my first session with trainer Leigh, she truly has a gift in personal training. I felt extremely comfortable working out with her. It can be kind of intimidating to work out at a gym but she made me feel at ease and she made feel like I could do anything I set my mind too. All my worries were out the window 5 minutes into our session. She worked me out, I worked up a sweat and I felt the burrrrnnnn. If you want a great looking butt and great looking bod PLUS a healthy lifestyle..Leigh is your trainer !
